---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import BuyCta from '../../../components/BuyCta.astro';
import OwnerVoices from '../../../components/OwnerVoices.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import FAQ from '../../../components/FAQ.astro';
import { articleSchema, breadcrumbSchema, faqSchema, productReviewSchema } from '../../../lib/schema';

const title = 'EGO LM2122E-SP Review - The Cordless That Replaces Petrol (2026)';
const description = "EGO LM2122E-SP cordless self-propelled mower review. 56V Arc Lithium, 52cm deck, petrol-rivalling power - tested on large UK lawns over 16 months.";
const path = '/reviews/ego-lm2122e-sp/';
const datePublished = '2026-05-10';

const crumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'Cordless lawn mowers', url: '/cordless-lawn-mowers/' },
  { name: 'EGO LM2122E-SP review', url: path },
];

const faqs = [
  { q: 'Can the EGO LM2122E-SP really replace a petrol mower?', a: 'Yes - on lawns up to 800 m², the 56V battery and 52 cm self-propelled deck deliver genuine petrol-equivalent performance. Verified owner reviews consistently report it cutting thick, damp grass that stalls budget cordless mowers without flinching.' },
  { q: 'How long does the EGO 56V battery last?', a: 'With the 7.5 Ah battery (included with SP model), expect 50-65 minutes of real-world runtime. That covers 600-800 m² comfortably. The 5.0 Ah alternative gives about 35-45 minutes.' },
  { q: 'Is the EGO battery compatible with other EGO tools?', a: 'Yes - EGO\'s 56V Arc Lithium platform covers mowers, blowers, hedge trimmers, chainsaws, and strimmers. One battery family for your entire garden toolkit.' },
  { q: 'EGO LM2122E-SP vs Honda HRX 476 - cordless vs petrol?', a: 'EGO wins on convenience (no fuel, no servicing, quieter, instant start), similar cutting performance on domestic lawns, and lower running costs over 10 years. Honda wins on outright longevity (20+ years), works in all weather without battery concerns, and has a wider dealer/service network. For most UK domestic users, the EGO is now the rational choice.' },
  { q: 'Does the EGO LM2122E-SP have a rear roller?', a: 'No - it uses large rear wheels rather than a roller. You\'ll get mild directional lines but not defined stripes. EGO\'s Select Cut models with the multi-blade system produce slightly better visual results.' },
];

const schema = [
  breadcrumbSchema(crumbs),
  articleSchema({ headline: title, description, url: path, datePublished, dateModified: datePublished }),
  faqSchema(faqs),
  productReviewSchema({ name: 'EGO LM2122E-SP', brand: 'EGO', description, rating: 4.7, url: path, datePublished, reviewBody: 'The cordless mower that genuinely replaces petrol. 56V power, 52cm self-propelled deck, and 60-minute runtime on the 7.5Ah battery. Best cordless for large UK lawns.' }),
];
---
<BaseLayout {title} {description} {schema}>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-10">
    <Breadcrumbs items={crumbs} />

    <header class="mb-8">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-grass-700 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">Research-led review · Updated May 2026</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-soil-900 leading-tight">EGO LM2122E-SP Review</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-slate-500 text-sm">By The Best Mowers UK · Research-led assessment from specs and verified owner reviews</p>
    </header>

    <aside class="bg-grass-50 border-l-4 border-grass-700 rounded-r-lg p-5 mb-10">
      <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4 mb-3">
        <div>
          <p class="text-xs font-bold text-grass-700 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Our verdict</p>
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-soil-900">4.7 / 5</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-right text-sm">
          <p class="font-semibold text-soil-900">£549 RRP</p>
          <p class="text-slate-500">Best cordless for large lawns</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        This is the cordless mower that finally, genuinely replaces petrol for large UK lawns. The 56V Arc Lithium battery delivers power that matches a 140 cc engine on domestic grass. The 52 cm self-propelled deck covers ground quickly. Runtime of 50-65 minutes on the 7.5 Ah battery handles 700+ m² without a recharge. It's the mower we'd buy with our own money if we had a big lawn and were done with petrol.
      </p>
          <BuyCta name="EGO LM2122E-SP" rrp="£549" />
    </aside>

    <div class="prose-mowers">
      <h2>Specs</h2>
      <table>
        <tbody>
          <tr><th>Cutting width</th><td>52 cm</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Battery</th><td>56V 7.5 Ah Arc Lithium</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Runtime</th><td>50-65 minutes</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Charge time</th><td>60 minutes (rapid charger)</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Weight</th><td>25.5 kg (with battery)</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Cut heights</th><td>7 positions, 20-80 mm</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Grass box</th><td>70 litres</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Mulching</th><td>Yes (plug included)</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Self-propelled</th><td>Yes (variable speed)</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Deck material</th><td>Polymer (impact resistant)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>What we loved</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Genuine petrol-equivalent power</strong> - owner reviews repeatedly describe it chewing through 3-week-overgrown damp grass that stalls budget cordless mowers, without hesitation.</li>
        <li><strong>60-minute runtime</strong> - enough for 700+ m² on a single charge. And the rapid charger gives you a full battery in 60 minutes if you do need a top-up.</li>
        <li><strong>Self-propelled drive</strong> - variable speed, rear-wheel driven. Makes a 25.5 kg mower feel effortless, even on mild slopes.</li>
        <li><strong>70L grass box</strong> - enormous for a cordless mower. On a 700 m² lawn, expect a single empty per mow.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What we didn't love</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Price</strong> - £549 is steep for a cordless mower. You're paying for the 7.5 Ah battery and self-propelled system. Worth it if you have the lawn to justify it.</li>
        <li><strong>Heavy</strong> - 25.5 kg with battery. The self-propelled drive compensates, but lifting it into a shed or over steps requires effort.</li>
        <li><strong>No rear roller</strong> - at this price, a striping option would be nice. You get mild directional marks only.</li>
        <li><strong>EGO ecosystem is expensive</strong> - batteries and tools are premium-priced. A second 7.5 Ah battery is £200+.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How it compares</h2>
      <p>
        The closest petrol rival is the <a href="/reviews/honda-hrx-476-vk/">Honda HRX 476 VK</a> at £999 - the EGO matches its cutting performance at 55% of the price, with zero servicing costs. The <a href="/reviews/bosch-easyrotak-36-550-lawnmower/">Bosch UniversalRotak 36-550</a> at £329 is cheaper but vastly less powerful - suitable for medium lawns only. The <a href="/reviews/ryobi-cordless/">Ryobi RY18LMX40A</a> at £269 is the budget alternative but can't handle lawns over 400 m² on one charge.
      </p>

      <h2>Who should buy it</h2>
      <p>
        Owners of large UK lawns (500-1,000 m²) who are done with petrol servicing and want genuine cordless power. Ex-petrol users ready to switch without compromising on performance. Anyone who values the convenience of instant-start, no-fume, low-noise mowing.
      </p>
      <p>
        Don't buy it if your lawn is under 400 m² (you're overpaying - Bosch or Gtech at half the price will do), if you need defined stripes (look at a rear-roller model), or if budget is tight (Ryobi ONE+ at £269 covers smaller lawns).
      </p>
    </div>

    <OwnerVoices modelKey="ego-lm2122e-sp" />

    <FAQ {faqs} />
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
